# LiVEiT® Logo Specifications

The LiVEiT® logo is the primary visual identifier of the LiVEiT® Framework.

It should be presented consistently across all platforms to maintain recognition, professionalism and brand integrity.

This document defines the official specifications for the LiVEiT® logo family.

---

# Official Logo

The official LiVEiT® wordmark is the primary logo of the framework.

It should be used whenever space permits and should not be recreated, redrawn or modified.

Only official artwork supplied within this repository should be used.

---

# Logo Variations

The official logo library consists of approved variations for different applications.

These include:

* Primary Logo
* Monochrome Logo
* White Logo
* Black Logo
* Icon Only
* Horizontal Layout
* Stacked Layout (where applicable)

No additional variations should be created without approval from the LiVEiT® project.

---

# Preferred Usage

The primary logo should always be the first choice.

Alternative versions should only be used when required by the background colour, available space or production method.

Examples include:

* White logo on dark backgrounds.
* Black logo on light backgrounds.
* Monochrome logo for single-colour printing.
* Icon-only version where space is limited.

---

# Backgrounds

The logo should always remain clearly visible against its background.

Suitable backgrounds include:

* White
* Black
* Neutral greys
* Official LiVEiT® brand colours
* Clean photographic imagery with sufficient contrast

Avoid placing the logo on visually complex backgrounds that reduce legibility.

---

# File Formats

Official logos are provided in multiple formats to suit different applications.

| Format | Purpose                                       |
| ------ | --------------------------------------------- |
| SVG    | Websites, applications and scalable graphics  |
| PNG    | Digital use with transparency                 |
| JPG    | Websites, Digital use                         |
| PDF    | Print production                              |

SVG should be used wherever possible for digital projects.

---

# Aspect Ratio

The logo must always retain its original proportions.

Never:

* Stretch the logo horizontally.
* Stretch the logo vertically.
* Compress the logo.
* Rotate the logo.
* Skew the logo.

Scaling should always be proportional.

---

# Colour integrity of the official logo

Only official logo colours may be used.

Do not:

* Replace brand colours.
* Apply gradients unless supplied in an official logo.
* Add outlines.
* Add shadows.
* Apply glow effects.
* Change opacity.

Any visual effects must be part of the official artwork.

---

# Placement

The logo should be positioned where it can be easily recognised without competing with surrounding content.

Allow sufficient space around the logo to maintain clarity.

Detailed spacing requirements are defined in the **Clear Space** section of this Branding Guide.

---

# Digital Applications

For websites, applications and user interfaces:

* Use SVG whenever possible.
* Maintain crisp rendering.
* Do not export unnecessarily large raster images.
* Preserve transparency where appropriate.

---

# Print Applications

For printed material:

* Use vector artwork whenever possible.
* Avoid low resolution images.
* Ensure sufficient contrast against the background.
* Maintain proportional scaling.

---

# Official Assets

Only logos provided through the official LiVEiT® repository should be considered authentic.

If a required variation does not exist, request a new official asset rather than creating one manually.

---

# Registered Trademark

LiVEiT® is a registered trademark.

The official logo is protected intellectual property and may not be modified, recreated or used in a manner that implies endorsement, ownership or affiliation without permission.

Refer to the Trademark and Commercial Licensing sections of this Branding Guide for further guidance.
